    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-10T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-10T08:30:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–1053: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AGV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d776fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-10T19:00:00+05:30"
                            >August 10, 1953—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>282. … <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> claims to have in hand positive
                    documentary proof American intrigues in Kashmir and that these documents will
                    not be used unless <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> is challenged by US for
                    proof.</p>
                <p>Embassy has … learned … that … Thursday, <persName corresp="#p_NJ1"
                        >Nehru</persName> was inclined to follow cautious policy vis-à-vis rift in
                        <persName corresp="#p_ASM1">Abdullah</persName> Cabinet but that <persName
                        corresp="#p_KDKN1">Katju</persName>, Tyagi and <persName corresp="#p_DSC1"
                        >C. D. Deshmukh</persName> were able to win him over to active policy by
                    showing him documents in question. He was already prone to accept reports of
                    American interference, particularly through Stevenson visit, and gave his OK for
                    ousting of <persName corresp="#p_ASM1">Abdullah</persName> and appointment of
                    Bakshi, according to prearranged plan made when Bakshi visited Delhi three weeks
                    ago.</p>
                <p>A. V. Pai, Secretary to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> Cabinet, is said to
                    have visited Kashmir for few hours August 7 to put finishing touches on plan and
                    give <persName>Karan Singh</persName> go ahead.</p>
                <p>I consider it advisable for US to take prompt action to counteract reports of US
                    interference and suggest I be authorized to deliver letter to <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> expressing confidence that both <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> and US Governments are equally anxious to
                    correct false impression of American interference and requesting any information
                        <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> may have on this subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
